TY  - JOUR
AU  - Mihov, Atanas
T1  -  Predisclosure Accumulations by Activist Investors and Price Impact of Trading *
PY  - 2016
Y1  - 2016/03/01
DO  - 10.1093/rof/rfv006
JO  - Review of Finance
JA  - Rev Financ
VL  - 20
IS  - 1
SP  - 231
EP  - 263
SN  - 1572-3097
AB  -  This study presents novel, robust evidence on the effect of price impact of trading, or Kyle’s lambda, on activist hedge funds’ predisclosure ownership accumulations. 1 We find that hedge fund investors are less likely to target illiquid firms; upon targeting an illiquid firm, activists choose private transactions to limit the price impact of their trades; upon doing open market transactions, the activist investors buy more shares of those firms with liquid stock. Our study suggests that market impact can be a factor with significant implications for shareholder activism, and more generally, corporate governance. 
Y2  - 3/26/2024
UR  - https://doi.org/10.1093/rof/rfv006
ER  - 



