AU  - Manconi, Alberto
AU  - Massa, Massimo
AU  - Zhang, Lei
T1  -  Bondholder Concentration and Credit Risk: Evidence from a Natural Experiment *
PY  - 2016
Y1  - 2016/03/01
DO  - 10.1093/rof/rfv010
JO  - Review of Finance
JA  - Rev Financ
VL  - 20
IS  - 1
SP  - 127
EP  - 159
SN  - 1572-3097
AB  - We exploit the impact of hurricane Katrina on insurance companies to study the relationship between bondholder concentration and credit risk. Redemption-driven sales by property and casualty (re)insurance companies exposed to hurricane Katrina are associated with a large drop in bondholder concentration faced by corporate bond issuers. Exploiting this shock to capture exogenous variation in bondholder concentration, we find that greater bondholder concentration is associated with higher bond yield spreads, as well as with firm characteristics associated with credit risk.
Y2  - 3/26/2024
UR  - https://doi.org/10.1093/rof/rfv010
ER  - 



