TY  - JOUR
AU  - Dangl, Thomas
AU  - Wu, Youchang
T1  -  Corporate Investment over the Business Cycle *
PY  - 2016
Y1  - 2016/03/01
DO  - 10.1093/rof/rfv003
JO  - Review of Finance
JA  - Rev Financ
VL  - 20
IS  - 1
SP  - 337
EP  - 371
SN  - 1572-3097
AB  - The average capital growth rate across firms declines sharply during a recession, and recovers only slowly. We provide a micro-founded explanation for this and several new stylized facts of investment asymmetry. Our investment model features various degrees of reversibility, cyclical macroeconomic shocks, and uncertainty about the state of the economy. Model simulations replicate strikingly different empirical patterns of capital growth rates at the aggregate and firm levels, featuring no slope asymmetry and a positive level asymmetry at the firm level, negative slope and level asymmetries at the aggregate level, and a positive relation between the industry-level slope asymmetry and asset illiquidity.
Y2  - 3/26/2024
UR  - https://doi.org/10.1093/rof/rfv003
ER  - 



